r.d: teds (Tentative Extra Data Structures) is a collection of data structures and iterable functionality
r.n: * Backwards incompatible change: Change `Deque` APIs to be consistent with SplDoublyLinkedList and `array_push`: change pushBack/popBack/pushFront/popFront to push/pop/unshift/shift * Backwards incompatible change: Remove `$preserve_keys` flag from `Vector::__construct` (Always reindex keys in order of iteration instead). * Add isEmpty() method to datastructures * Make exceeding the capacity limit for a vector a fatal error. * Make Deque::push() and unshift() variadic.
